"What is he talking about?" CRYOTEK said as he looked at TARANTULUS
and ANTAGONY.

"Well, it seems as if there is a rip and we cannot communicate with
Cybertron. " TARANTULUS said as he wiggled his finger together
nervously.

ANTAGONY sighed exasperatedly, "There is a temporal rip occurring
here." She said as she stepped forward, "And we don't have time for me
to keep explaining it to every new person that comes into the room.
Keep up or take notes."

CRYOTEK glanced again at TARANTULUS, "So that is what this is about. I
have suspected something like that when I found pod." He was talking
about ANTAGONY. "She had a temporal signature unlike anything I have
ever detected."

"So that means that you believe me?" TARANTULUS said as he regained
some of his composure.

There was a dark smile from CRYOTEK, "Of course I do."

"Then we can get looking for . . " ANTAGONY said.

" . . . No!" CRYOTEK cut in smoothly, "You will answer all my
questions first and then we will consider what to do."

TARANTULUS straightened, "I have the canons here.," He gestured at the
weapons that were even now orienting on CRYOTEK as well. "I decide
what we do."

"Do you now?" CRYOTEK said as his dark smile acquired more humor.
"These are my weapons and my codes drive them." He pulled out a device
and aimed it at the weapons and then they deactivated. "And they fire
on only whom *I* tell them to."

TARANTULUS stepped back a step, "I . . . see." He said and then fell silent.

Turning back to ANTAGONY there was a nod from CRYOTEK, "Now you have
many questions to answer."

ANTAGONY straightened, "And if I refuse?"

"I would expect you to do that." CRYOTEK gestured to the DINOBOT, "Take her."

(TAG)

- Preston
